headline: Zoetis Stock Is Falling. Why the Animal-Health Company Was Downgraded.
summary: It’s shaping up to be a dog-eat-dog world for  Zoetis  as the maker of veterinary medicine faces stiff competition in the animal health market.  Zoetis  was created in 2013 after splitting off from  Pfizer’s  animal health division.  In fact, Zoetis has proven to be even more profitable than Merck’s animal health division as of late.

headline: Zoetis downgraded amid slowing growth concerns, intensifying competition
